gomodel:SYNGO_981  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3 shows that by quantitative electron microscopy that in slices from αCaMKII KO mice, asymmetric synapses on dendritic spines of CA1 pyramidal neurons, the number of docked vesicles is increased. Figure S4 shows example images.\n\nFigure 2d show that during a 10 Hz train, the depletion rate of SVs is lower in slices from αCaMKII KO mice.\n\nTaken together, these data point to a regulatory role of αCaMKII on synaptic vesicle docking.\n\n2/7/2017 Pim\n- Important to note that this effect on SV docking is not depending on its catalytic activity.. Experimental description: From the supplemental file:\n'To study the role of presynaptic αCaMKII, we made use of a αCaMKII mutant, in which αCaMKII exon 2 is deleted7. Exon 2 encodes the catalytic site, and deletion of this exon results in a premature translation stop due to a frame shift, thus effectively resulting in a αCaMKII knock-out (KO) line7.' 'All mice were obtained by breeding heterozygous parents.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2017-07-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_981" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

